        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "The dishes aren't coming out clean, what's wrong?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most common cause is the filter assembly at the bottom of the tub, food debris accumulates and restricts water flow to the spray arms. We pull and clean the filter, inspect the sump, and test the spray arm rotation. Second most common: clogged spray arm nozzles from hard LA water buildup, vinegar soak and flush. Third: failed circulation pump not producing full wash pressure. Fourth: the water heating element has failed and the wash is running cold (cold water doesn't dissolve detergent properly, common cause of film on glassware)."
