      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Thermador dishwasher repair, common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Are Thermador dishwashers the same as Bosch inside?</summary>
        <p>Very close. Both are made by BSH Home Appliances, historically in the same European factories, now in New Bern, NC for the Radiance Collection. Most Thermador service parts cross-reference with Bosch Benchmark, pumps, valves, heating elements, latches. We stock both. Thermador differentiators are Star Speed heater, Zeolite StarDry, tighter sound insulation, and branded electronics.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>My dishwasher won't drain</summary>
        <p>Start with the filter assembly at the bottom of the tub, 80% of these calls end with filter cleaning and no parts. If the filter is clear, check the drain hose (kinks under the cabinet, blockage at the air gap or disposal). Failed drain pump motor is next ($245–$325). We diagnose by running a drain cycle and listening at the pump for the characteristic whine.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Dishes aren't getting clean, films and spots</summary>
        <p>Filter first (restricted water flow to spray arms). Then spray arm nozzle cleaning (LA hard water mineral buildup). Then heating element test (if wash water isn't reaching 140°F detergent doesn't dissolve). Fourth, rinse aid dispenser refill and flow check. Most clean-result calls resolve without replacement parts.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Thermador dishwasher repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common jobs: wash pump $385–$525, drain pump $245–$325, heating element $220–$310, door latch $215–$295, control board $485–$680. Full pricing table above.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Error E15 or E22, what do they mean?</summary>
        <p>E15 is water in the base pan, flood protection tripped. Source-trace the leak (inlet valve gasket, sump, door seal, pump housing) before resetting. E22 is a drain/filter clog, clear the filter, verify the drain hose, test the drain pump. Neither code is a parts-replacement default, both usually resolved with cleaning and leak inspection.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>The Home Connect app isn't working</summary>
        <p>Almost always router-side or firmware-level, not hardware. We reset the WiFi module, re-pair to network, check for stalled firmware updates. Actual WiFi module replacement is about 5% of connectivity calls ($165 if needed).</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How fast can you come out?</summary>
        <p>Same-day on calls before 1 PM weekday in regular coverage. Dishwashers are lower-priority than refrigerators or range failures, but we still usually fit you in same-afternoon.</p>
      </details>
